# Configuration Steps

### 1. Check/Install Package

Verify if the package is installed:
`rpm -qa telnet-*`

### 2. Install Telnet (if not installed)

Install the service using:
`yum install telnet-* -Y`

### 3. Enable and Start the Socket

`systemctl enable telnet.socket`
`systemctl start telnet.socket`

check the status 
`systemctl status telnet.socket`

### 4. Configure Firewall

Allow traffic on TCP port 23:
`firewall-cmd --permanent --add-port=23/tcp`
`firewall-cmd --reload`

### 5. Verify

Test the connection locally or from a remote host:
`telnet 192.168.29.10`

### 6. Connect from Windows Machine
Enable telnet in Windows features from control panel

Deploy the telnet client in Windows Command Prompt (as Administrator):
`dism /online /enable-feature /enable:telnetclient` #deploy image service management (DISM)

Connect to the windows machine:
`telnet 192.168.29.10`
enter username & password 

